<p><ent>Railing</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Railing
<hw>Rail"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A barrier made of a
rail or of rails, together with vertical supports. The typical railing
in the interior of structures or on porches has a horizontal rail near
waist height, and multiple vertical supports. Its function is usually to
provide a safety barrier at the edge of a verticle drop to prevent
falls.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Rails in general; also, material for making
rails.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Railingly</ent>⟦br⟧
